The paper deals with compressed sensing signal recovery, which is a topic that falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a novel approach called Forward-Backward Pursuit (FBP), which is a type of iterative algorithm that falls under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also includes simulations for the recovery of a sparse image, which falls under the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves optimization techniques, which fall under the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category.
